<title type="html"><![CDATA[Classic Shell and Win 7 Ultimate SP1 64 Bit]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1650&amp;p=8456#p8456"><![CDATA[
Hi<br /><br />I think this is a bug and apologise if you consider I have posted in the wrong place.<br /><br />I have been running Classic Shell for a couple of years on my Notebook with no problems until now. I have been trying to update to the latest version.<br /><br />I have a problem with updating / installing Classic Shell onto my Notebook running Windows 7 Ultimate SP1 64 Bit.<br />I can see there has been some discussion on this issue but cannot find any solutions.<br /><br />When I run the latest update ClassicShellSetup_4_0_2.exe, I get the following error message: Failed to run msiexec.exe<br />I researched this and was recommended to extract ClassicShell 4.0.2 and run the .msi package (ClassicShellSetup64_4_0_2.msi) and when I try to do that, I get through the first steps of the set up until the Install package finds two versions of Windows Explorer running. I then select either of the two options offered and get the following results:<br />i. Close the applications and attempt to restart them<br />When I select this option the install closes Windows Explorer (the Tool Bar, system tray and Start Button, and then then after calculating space the install says there are 2 versions of Windows Explorerer and I select this option, and the system returns error 2605 and stops.. and I have to log out (Cnt + Alt + Delete) and log back in.<br /><br />ii. Do not close the applications. A reboot will be required<br />When i select this option, I also get to the point where I get an error code 2605, and when I click OK the system uninstalls where it got to and closes. <br /><br />The strange thing is when the uninstall stops the previous Classic Shell menu is there but corrupted. I can see the Classic Start Menu running but the Menu options all start with $ .. for example $Menu.Help and so on.<br /><br />I really do like Classic Shell and hope you can help resolve the problem.<br /><br />Daniel<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2111">|Roo</a> — Tue Nov 05, 2013 3:19 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
